entment-a modern form of racism that has superseded the old-fashioned biological variety-is a potent political force.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPresidentszUnited StatesxElectiony2008. 0aRacexPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aRacismxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 7aHISTORY / United States / 21st Century.2bisacsh1 aDale-Riddle, Allison, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030017519640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018359740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300183597423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300183597/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY